This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring May 1, 2010, as Loyalty Day. The proclamation highlights the importance of loyalty to the United States and its values. It references the history of the national seal and the symbolism of the eagle with the motto "E Pluribus Unum" (Out of many, one). The proclamation also emphasizes the common ideals that bind Americans together, such as individual equality, constitutional liberty, and the rule of law. It acknowledges the sacrifices made by loyal Americans in preserving the Union and defending freedom. The proclamation calls upon the people of the United States to observe Loyalty Day by displaying the flag of the United States and pledging allegiance to the Republic.